de_dust2_2082

A recreation from "dust to dust"
After many hours of hard work I'm proud to announce my contest entry for the "Time traveler mapping contest" .
de\_dust2\_2082 is a recreation of the well known map de\_dust2, 70 years into the future.


Created from scratch

Believe it or not, but every single piece of brushwork within the map has been built from scratch; I literally built the entire original level from the ground up, before the enjoyment of smashing it down. It was a long, and highly tedious process but I am pleased with the result.
To display my progress throughout the project I have recorded a time-lapse of the entire project. From the first steps all the way to final optimization. This video will be posted either tomorrow or later in the week \- as soon as I have time.

The Map

The map is fully optimized, containing spawnpoints to support up to 64 players and includes a wide range of custom content and ideas. The map also features a dynamic sandstorm system to vary the standard gameplay of de\_dust2.
The overall game objective remains the same, Plant and defuse \- at the same locations as the original map, though that doesn\'t mean a lot has not changed\...
The Terrorists managed to successfully bomb B Square at Mars, 2016 \- resulting in a war between 2016 \- 2020 within the country. Over the next twenty years the majority of the country was rebuilt; though the streets of dust were left as rubble.
The year is now 2082. A reconstruction company have found and begun reconstruction of the lost town attempting to recreate the buildings to their former charm. During this long process they stumbled across crates containing the remnants of a unique weapon from the previous. A weapon so powerful that it could remove the whole region from the map. Don't let the terrorists ruin this, defend the areas and get away with those crates, before they do the same.

Features:


  • 64 Spawnpoints
  • color correction
  • custom .nav file for bots
  • soundscapes
  • custom textures (a few)
  • loads of detail
  • a well optimized level
  • custom motd
  • custom radar overview
  • HDR
  • 3D skybox
  • Sandstorms! spawning randomly after 90sec
  • and more
Please rate, comment, subscribe and wish me the best of luck in the contest!
I hope you like it!
Cheers! - Alex

Making this map was a real challenge, since Ace and myself are on Linux. We made this map only using this operation system and using Hammer through Wine.

This maps is a complex bomb scenario map intended to offers a different gameplay from the official ones. Indeed, this map is not as open as the official ones but there are a lot more possibilities.

In this map the layout will be generated randomly on each round in order to offer a more complex and original gameplay.

On the graphic side, this map was inspired by old school brush-work level-design such as Half Life. And we have put a particular attention to the optimization, thus this map can be played on a very low end computer with decent frame-rates.

Also a hand-made Navigation-Mesh is included in order to play with bots !

If you want to contact us in order to get the .vmf for educational or remix purposes you can check our E-M@ils in the .txt contained in the archive !

_aChangeLog.text: not solid prop changed to solid prop

_aLatestUpdates._sText: Im very upset right now.. I was amidst finalizing a really nice nav map for cs_drn0s_nuclear_facility when i found that a prop_static model of a push cart was NOT SOLID. I was immediately irritated because now the nav mesh i spent an hour on and all four map versions needed to have this F*#king changed to  prop_dynamic SOLID. This prop was smack in the middle of a main bomb sight/hostage rescue room entrance. i feel stupid as hell and know its because i smoke tha mad buhds that i some how missed this damn prop. so now ive quickly wasted over an hour updating all 4 maps getting them onto the server the b2z files for download the zips for here and the zips for the vmfs of the maps all repacked and uploaded to their respective areas. these maps i swear to god i hope are F#*king DONE because i cant stand to continue to update this damn map!?!! On a brighter side note. ive almost well-enough figured out how to truly optimize a nav mesh. certain areas needed new nav areas made and i needed to remove alot of areas to remake the areas so honestly changing the prop and ruining all the bsp versions was almost a faster route than reiterating the nav meshes there compared to a completely nav_generated mesh lol. so.. now with this update. hopefully ill never have to change any of the .bsps ever again. and hopefully the next package i upload will be nav meshes for all four maps. im starting with cs_drn0s because the hostages are requiring more work to create the path ways and if more demanding than the other map styles. so. Cheers and Heres to hopefully never changing this map again and finally being finished with the damn thing!

de_drainagecanal_V4 Story

Local union canal workers refused to cooperate with the mafia when asked to ignore shipments of illegal substances and weapons into the city. In response the mob scouted out an old waste drain canal that is below the current waterline. This place is filled with a bunch of trash,toxins and cars that went over the edge due to the awkward road layout. The only thing separating it from the general canal system is a meager pair of locks that the goons need to blow all the way to St. Paul. If the canal water fills the waste basin it can flood the toxins back into homes and by the time the canal company contain the incident the entire canal system will be oozing with sludge bringing it to a halt. The insuing cleanup effort could run the company (that is already short on cash) into the ground allowing the mafia to aquisition it, giving them a method to ship anything they want into the city with or without union support. Another target conveniently located nearby is a small company office belonging to the same canal company. If it is destroyed it could show the union that the mafia means business, Intimidated by said action the CWU will no doubt cooperate.

T objectives:
-Destroy locks and flood contents of waste basin into the canal system and nearby buildings.
-Destroy canal company office to show Union that you're not F***king around.
-Eliminate resistance.

CT objectives:
-Protect the canal company's property.
-Eliminate resistance.

Locations of interest:
-Small store near T spawn.
-Double Star Hotel. (2-story hotel near T spawn)
-Hostel. (belongs to some Yugoslav or something, doesn't matter if it blows up)
-Drain Canal. (beware of the water, it just can't be safe to wade in it)
-Locks. (send them to the heavens via C4 express)
-Canal Company Office. (them too also)
-Abandoned store. (near police station, really dark, good hiding spot)
-Housing Projects. (doorways make for good cover)
-Bridges. (they get you over the canals don't they? So don't complain!)
-Drain tunnel 483. (goes from under one of the bridges to the locks, also has a passage to the office, posesses major tactical importance, BE SURE TO BRING FLASHLIGHT!)
